Former Deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas has resigned as Member of Parliament.The office of the African National Congress (ANC) Chief Whip confirmed on Thursday. The office said Jonas resignation took effect on 31 March. The Office of the ANC Chief Whip confirms the resignation of former Deputy Finance Minister and ANC MP Cde Mcebisi Jonas as a member of parliament effective 31 March 2017, the statement read.Jonas&#8217; resignation comes a day after former Transport Minister Dipuo Peter s resignation. Both Jonas and Peters were removed from their positions as Transport Minister and Deputy Minister during the recent cabinet reshuffle.Peters was replaced by Joe Maswanganyi, a former MEC of Sports, Arts and Culture in Limpopo. Jonas was replaced by Sifiso Buthelezi.The Chief whip s office said Jonas served both as Deputy Minister and MP with absolute distinction and dedication, adding that he also served South African people in various capacities over the years. On behalf of the ANC in Parliament we thank comrade Jonas for his selfless service to the movement as its public representative.We are confident that he will continue serving the country and our movement in other capacities in future. We wish him well, the office emphasised.-Sipho Jack